steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"7v8pe","text":"Fixation: Use fresh 4% PFA solution in PBS (w/ or wo/ 4% sucrose) for 15-20 min. Wash 3 times in PBS and quench aldehydes with glycine or sodium borate.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":10}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3k95d","text":"Permeabilize in blocking buffer (0.2% fish gelatin, 0.1% or 0.3% triton in PBS), 1 hr at RT.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fcrsq","text":"Incubate with primary antibodies in blocking buffer 1h at RT, or overnight at 4ºC.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"ajpgs","text":"Wash slices with blocking buffer, 4 times, ~10 min each.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"64kp7","text":"Incubate slice with secondary antibodies in blocking buffer 1 h at RT on a shaker.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8h4o0","text":"Dilute AcX 1:100 (0.1 mg/mL) in 1x PBS (prepare 500 uL/well for 12-well plates).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"12l2","text":"Treat stained expressing genetically encoded FPs slices or coverslips for \u003e 6 hours at RT (this reaction can be left overnight).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5taok","text":"Wash 2x 15 minutes with PBS before proceeding to gelation. Samples can be stored at 4º C.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"arlhf","text":"Make sure to remove excess PBS from brain slices before incubation with gelling solution. Incubate slices in gelling solution in a 24-well plate for 25 min at 4C. Coverslips with cells can be mounted directly.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4q6hu","text":"Create a humid gel chamber. For 50 um slices, 2 coverglass were used to create a 170 um-depth sandwich chamber. Cell cultures were mounted cells side-down over a drop of gel (35 um for a coverslip of 12 mm). Make sure the slices are flat, and avoid air bubbles trapped inside the chamber.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1rhhp","text":"Cover the gel in digesting buffer for 15 min and add proteinase K for and overnight incubation @ room temperature (make sure at least 10-fold excess volume of digestion buffer is used, and make sure make it does not dry out).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fgq6m","text":"Wash slices with excess volume of ddH2O (we usually use at least 10x the final gel volume), 3-5 times, for 15mins each time. Slice expansion reaches plateau after about the 3rd or 4th wash. The expansion chamber needs to be of adequate size for the sample: hemislices of mouse brains fit nicely in a 6-well plate when the excess gel around the brain is trimmed away (a razor blade works well for this). 18 mm coverslips can be punched in 4 mm medals before expansion to get gels of around 16 mm.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8ir85","text":"Use a cleaned coverslip and add poly-L-lysine 0.1% solution to the top surface for 20-30 min. Rinse with ddH2O and air dry. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ili0","text":"Remove excess of liquid around the gel and place the expanded sample on the coverslip. After 20-30 sec, add ddH2O to keep the sample hydrated.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
